        "id": 2908442,
        "name": "Nick Catanzariti",
        "username": "N_Catanzariti",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/46a35a/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-06-08T12:12:00.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Delving into purchasing wine at auction and have a specific bottle, 1990 Chateau de Beaucastel that I am very interested in purchasing.  It is my birth year wine which is being celebrated next month.  The only remarks on the bottle is 3cm ullage.  There is no evidence of seeping or stains on the labels and the auction says it was purchased at retail and stored in a temperature controlled storage unit.   With this being my first time buying an older vintage wine at auction, I was not sure how significant a 3cm ullage is on a 30 year old bottle.  Can anyone provide some suggestions on what to do based on experience?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T19:31:56.921Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
        "reply_to_post_number": null,
