      {
        "id": 2908453,
        "name": "Fred Bower",
        "username": "Fred_Bower",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/fred_bower/{size}/100288_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-06-08T12:33:57.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The storage notes seem like boilerplate text that you see for just about every auction lot.  I\u2019d take them as having limited value.  3cm isn\u2019t an unreasonable amount of ullage on a wine of this age in my book.  I like to enjoy birth year wine on my birthday.  I\u2019ve had a few that were duds, but more good than bad.  I\u2019d go for it and continue to keep an eye out for your vintage to accumulate a few for coming years.</p>\n<p>Cheers and happy birthday!<br>\nfred</p>",
